safenet.jhsm.constants

Class HSMS

  • java.lang.Object
    • safenet.jhsm.constants.HSM_STATE
      • safenet.jhsm.constants.HSMS

  • public class HSMS
extends HSM_STATE
    Class defining HSMS_STATE constants.

    Further information concerning the various attribute types is provided in the ProtectProcessing Orange Programmer's Manual.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static HSMS FIPS_MODE
      The firmware is started, and the HSM_STATE is in FIPS mode.
      static HSMS HALT
      The HSM_STATE is halted due to a failure.
      static HSMS MTF_MODE
      The HSM_STATE contains a Manufacturing Test Firmware, and it is started.
      static HSMS NONFIPS_MODE
      The HSM_STATE is in NON FIPS mode.
      static HSMS NORMAL_OPERATION
      The HSM_STATE is in one of the following three states: S_NONFIPS_MODE, S_WAIT_FOR_INIT, or S_FIPS_MODE.
      static HSMS POST
      The HSM_STATE is initializing, and performing POST (Power On Self Test).
      static HSMS POWER_OFF_WITH_KEYS
      Power off state, with key material stored in secure memory.
      static HSMS POWER_OFF_WITH_NO_KEYS
      Power off state, with no key material in the HSM_STATE.
      static HSMS TAMPER_RESPOND
      The HSM_STATE is responding to tamper.
      static HSMS WAIT_FOR_INIT
      The HSM_STATE has booted OK and is waiting for a C_Initialize.
      static HSMS WAIT_ON_TAMPER
      The HSM_STATE is waiting for the tamper cause to be removed.
